{"lemma":"سِيرَةٍ","slug":"سِيرَةٍ","root":"س.#.ر","root_slug":"س-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21411","n21417","n21418","n21419"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"biography, chronicle, romance","examples":[{"text":"وتشمل هذه المصادر المهمة السِيَرَ الذاتية الإسلامية التقليدية لمحمد، والتي توفر معلومات إضافية عن حياته.","english":"These important sources include the traditional Islamic biographies of Muhammad, which provide additional information about his life."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"profile (summary of information about a person)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conduct, way of living"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"walk, pleasure walk"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conversation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"traveling provisions"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ways and means"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"measures"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21411","headword_ar":"سيّرهُ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoyiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْيِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsArhu","text_ar":"اسارهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sArhu","text_ar":"سارهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorN","text_ar":"سَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapN","text_ar":"سِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaArN","text_ar":"مَسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapN","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrN","text_ar":"مَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as below]; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IJ, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, A, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to go"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any pace"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to go,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pass, along; to march, journey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceed; to go away, pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwra","text_ar":"سُورَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra bihi","text_ar":"سِيرَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reg. pass. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra bihi","text_ar":"سَارَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is mentioned; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwba","text_ar":"هُوبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwla","text_ar":"كُولَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~r","text_ar":"سيّر"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsArhA","text_ar":"اسارها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sArhA","text_ar":"سارها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorN","text_ar":"سَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapN","text_ar":"سِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaArN","text_ar":"مَسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrN","text_ar":"مَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapN","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as above]; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the beast to go"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (S, M, A, Msb:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirotu","text_ar":"سِرْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rode the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thus made it to go"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Ibn-Buzurj, TA:) but when you ride it to pasture, you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asarotuhaA","text_ar":"اَسَرْتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsrthA A_ilaY AlkalaA^i","text_ar":"اسرتها اـِلَى الكَلَاِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Buzurj, TA) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY AlmaroEaY","text_ar":"الى المَرْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~rhu mino baladihi","text_ar":"سيّرهُ مِنْ بَلَدِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to go,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depart, from his town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"country; expelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banished, him from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) ―         -b2-  [Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~r","text_ar":"سيّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the horsecloth, or covering, (S, A, K,) from the horse, (K,) or beast, (A,) or from the back of the beast. (S.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"a proverb, (K,) and a saying, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become current;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he published"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~r siyrapN","text_ar":"سيّر سِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He related stories of the ancients."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~rhu","text_ar":"سيّرهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorN","text_ar":"سَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ a thong ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made stripes upon it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a garment, or piece of cloth, and an arrow. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~arato xiDaAbahaA","text_ar":"سَيَّرَتْ خِضَابَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made her dye to have the form of stripes, like thongs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * A, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n21417","headword_ar":"سَيْرَةٌ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21418","headword_ar":"سِيرَةٌ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorN","text_ar":"سَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A going, in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any pace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see above:] a subst. from 1 in the first of the senses assigned to it above. (M, K.) Lh mentions the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHasanu Als~iyrapi","text_ar":"لَحَسَنُ السِّيرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is good in going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (M: in the TA, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayorapi","text_ar":"السَّيْرَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as having the meaning here next following.) ―         -b2-  Also, (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorapN","text_ar":"سَيْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [but the former seems to be the right, being agreeable with analogy, whereas the latter is anomalous,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (M, K.) ―         -b3-  And the former, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, rule, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqapN","text_ar":"طَرِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sun~apN","text_ar":"سُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyarN","text_ar":"سِيَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra bihimo siyrapF HasanapF","text_ar":"سَارَ بِهِمْ سِيرَةً حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued with them a good way of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra AlwaAliY fiY Alr~aEiy~ahi siyrapF HasanapF","text_ar":"سَارَ الوَالِى فِى الرَّعِيَّهِ سِيرَةً حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prefect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor, pursued among the subjects a good way of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A, Msb; *) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapF qabiyHapF","text_ar":"سِيرَةً قَبِيحَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad way of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"record of"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions and pious works;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the prefixed noun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyfap","text_ar":"صَحِيفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being understood. (Mgh.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stories of the ancients:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapu A^aw~aliyna","text_ar":"سِيرَةُ اَوَّلِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA fiY siyrapi AlA^aw~aliyna","text_ar":"هٰذَا فِى سِيرَةِ الاَوَّلِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is in the stories of the ancients"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-  [Hence it is used in the present day as meaning (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mention"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person or thing: and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a matter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subject, of discourse."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-  Also, as a law term, (Mgh,) or so [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyarN","text_ar":"سِيَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Military expeditions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"memorable actions thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iyaru Alkabiyru","text_ar":"السِّيَرُ الكَبِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The great book of military expeditions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iyaru Alkabiyru","text_ar":"السِّيَرُ الكَبِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; using a masc. epithet in lieu of the [suppressed] prefixed noun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAb","text_ar":"كِتَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b8-  Also, the sing., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of being; state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayoy^apN","text_ar":"هَيْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, Msb.) So in the Kur xx. 22. (M, O, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other provision, that is brought from a place to be laid up in store."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","Mgh","Msb","O"]},{"entry_id":"n21419","headword_ar":"سُيَرَةٌ","root":"syr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeys, much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great goer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IJ, M, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayuwrN","text_ar":"سَيُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied as an epithet [in the same sense] to a hackney, and to an ass. (Az, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frh","text_ar":"فره"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["IJ","M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}